<TITLE> 'Militant boss' killed in Pabna 'gunfight' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Pabna, August 24 (bdnews24.com)A 'gunfight' between alleged militants and RAB and police in Faridpur upazila of Pabna district early on Monday left Atiqul Islam Atiq, alleged leader of the group of militants known as 'Bahini', killed. Four members of RAB and police were injured, police said. Pabna police superintendent Nibash Chandra Majhi and RAB deputy director flight lieutenant Ahmed Faisal said, tipped off about a clandestine meeting of the 'Bahini' being held in Badal of Hadol union under Faridpur upazila at around 3am, a contingent of RAB-12 and police arrived there. The militants opened fire at them and the law enforcers retaliated. The gun battle continued for half an hour, leaving 'Bahini' boss Atiq, 40, dead on the spot and two RAB and as many police personnel wounded. The injured were given first aid. The law enforcers retrieved a handmade gun, two rounds of live ammo and sharp weapons from the spot. Atiq, son of Khorshed Sardar of Badal, had about a dozen cases filed against him with police stations of Pabna. bdn
